        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>The 
                <emph render="italic">Socialist News</emph> was formed by the merger of the 
                <emph render="italic">Cleveland Socialist</emph> and 
                <emph render="italic">Workers' Cause</emph>. It was published by first by the Local Cleveland, Socialist Party, beginning in 1914, then by the Local Cuyahoga County, Socialist Party, ending in 1919. The 
                <emph render="italic">Cleveland Plain Dealer</emph>, founded in 1845, is the largest daily newspaper in Ohio.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>This small collection contains photocopied material from a scrapbook containing clippings on local and national radical activity. The majority of the clippings come from the 
                <emph render="italic">Cleveland Plain Dealer</emph> and the 
                <emph render="italic">Socialist News of Cleveland</emph> with a few clippings from other papers local to the Cleveland, Ohio area. The clippings span from 1915-1919 with a few items from the mid-1920s. The original scrapbook, of unknown provenance, was in fragile and fading condition and was disbound and recopied. PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
